<plot>With no sound, with no dialogue, monologue or action, Nigel Tomm's film adaptation of James Frey's book "A Million Little Pieces" is the transfer of the story to the space of art. Somebody calls it absolute art. Somebody calls it abstract film. Somebody calls it fraud. Totally innocent yet completely alluring. Let your eyes judge the ultimate beauty.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?013284</url></doc>
